caption: This is Ruth Chris. Change the name from The Steakhouse.

Maybe I ordered the wrong thing but I am not impressed and will not go back.  I ordered the gumbo - priced at $16 - and had it delivered to my room.  It was the smallest amount of gumbo I have ever seen...barely a cup!  I was also charged $5 for delivery then they tacked on $3 gratuity and none of this is including tax!  I paid $26 for a mediocre cup of gumbo.

Great atmosphere and food. Comfortable booths and seating. Privacy if you need it. A great place to have a celebration type dinner with family or friends. I would recommend trying it out! Of course making a reservation is probably a good idea =).

We visited on 12-20-2020 @ 615 pm It was freezing 🥶 🥶 🥶in the resturant. The table we sit at was old & beat up. The place is just plain & dark NO LIFE. Crab cake was ok, the sauce overpowering. The pork chop & asparagus came out no heat 🔥  the sauce from the crab cake was the sauce on top of the pork chop, had to push the sauce off. Had a dirty fork under the table 🤔 The waitress 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽. The price for the meal👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾only reward members should eat here but we deserve BETTER.
Amazing place, great food, wonderful atmosphere, and amazing whiskey. Thank you for the amazing service Ruby!
Overpriced....better steaks at my house.
The food was awesome
It was so tasty. The staff was very welcoming and sociable. The place has a cool atmosphere.

Sad, when the only thing good about the meal was the coupon I used so it was free. My food was cold, my gumbo had shells in it and no shrimp, the temperature on my steak was way off, and my Caesars salad was not chopped. I purposely didn't order the wedge salad so I wouldn't have to cut it myself. My steak was more gristle than meat. I had to ask if there was cheese on my broccoli.

First time ive been there in 7 mos. New menu and staff. Different, but equally excellent. Oysters were great, our group also had the burger, ribeye, and filet, all cooked perfectly, staff attentive but not overbearing, when friends or family visit from out of town and want steak, this is my go to. Fantastic. Weird blue dog art, too.

Honestly? Not at all impressed. Husband and I got the ribeye steak with asparagus and fries. Put plainly-  the steak sucked. Lacked flavor, wasn’t cooked right, and we’ve definitely had better steaks priced lower than this. It simply wasn’t worth the $60 we paid for it. So we were very disappointed. The service was kind. Not too impressive, just good. I did like the ambiance though. Extremely modern, intimate and very private. But I wouldnt recommend the restaurant. Find another good steakhouse.
The steak was outstanding. The oyster were perfect. The EGGS!!! Oh the Eggs are so tasty.
Mark is a great bartender.  His service at the bar along with the excellent food made for ab awesome meal.
I ate here & the food was delicious. What made it even better was Ruby who made my dining experience truly wonderful. Thanks for making it so special.
The food was delicious.  The very best part was our server Ruby.  Ruby went above and beyond.   I highly recommend the Steakhouse and ask for Ruby.
Price is definitely worth it trust me great steaks

The Donut Sundae was one of the best desserts I have had in a while.  NY Strip was great however the $160 Wagyu Ribeye was not quite worth the price. The pork belly and lobster pasta were also very good.  Service was excellent and overall the meal was quite good.

Really disappointed at the Steakhouse in Harrah’s, I went for my birthday. We ordered the stone crabs which were excellent. My husband ordered a filet mignonette which was supposed to be medium and came to the table overcooked . I ordered the double pork chop which difficult to cut and dry. The side corn a crab risotto was great. The waitress Yama was 5 stars and was awesome. Besh Steakhouse was better . Will not go back. Go to Fleming’s.
To loud, wait even with reservations was to long and it was like they could have cared less if we were there or not.
Food was great... our waiter... not so much.
Great food and great prices.
The special is whole red snapper which is pretty good.  I order bone in ribeye but it's hard to chew probably grass fed. They do have Australia wagyu beef but cost $160.
We really enjoyed our steaks here was pleasantly surprised and got to use my Harrahs points to pay
EXCELLENT" Bill "is the Best !!!!

This review is strictly for the steak. Biggest red flag was having the steak come out cut in half because the cook doesnt know how to temp properly. Even after visually checking, it was underdone, which isn't as bad as overdone I guess.
Service slow but otherwise ok.
Overpriced steak place and cook can't get med rare right.
Food menu didn't have a lot of choices and the appetizers were terrible. My drink was good and the server was great.
Had to wait and the hostess snubbed us.

Delicious dinner! I chose from the Revellions Menu: caesar salad, steak mashed potatoes & vegetables and cheese cake all paired with wine tasting. Each course was delicious! The wine pairings were delectable.  A special thank you to Karla (hostess), Allie (server) and Anthony (server). Their wonderful service made the meal even better. Anthony was so very attentive and so much fun and Allie was very sweet. Karla was accommodating as she changed our seats because of the air conditioning cold air. Thanks again for making my dinner at The Steak House a fun adventure.
Service lousy staff rude food cold
Nice and friendly staffs.  Good wine selection.
The food was good,  the service was a little lacking, but the food was cooked just as ordered.

Food quality was below my expectations for the price. Rolls was burnt! I got the prime rib and it looked like a piece of steak from Waffle House. Ordered the corn and crab Risotto  it had no flavor. Was so disappointed! Service was average.
Excellent food, nice staff, consistently fantastic atmosphere. They charge fair prices and the food quality is excellent. 5 stars.
Excellent food and service!
The food is great and the staff is better
Great steak

So tasty

Very delicious food and great service!!!

Steak was ok. The service wasn't good at all. My waiter checked on me 2 times after delivering my meal. I waited 20 minutes for salt and pepper. Definitely wouldn't go back and spend my money there. There are many  other options nearby.
Our waiter, Ruby, was fantastic! Marie Boocoo!
One of the better Bone in Rib Eye's I've had in the city. Mark's service was excellent!
Really nice place

Great place for great food... If you have the time.

Ohhhh my God the steak and service was phenomenal!

Really impressed with the food and service. Cocktails were on point and the Steak was amazing. Filet was nice, tender, and did not disappoint!  Ask for Shawn if you stop by...she was awesome and had great recommendations for the entire group.  Also...credit to Belinda for recommending this place 😊

The host was very friendly! HOWEVER our server took 15 mins to greet us, once he did bring our drinks he never came back. Me and my husband were extremely upset, after 20 mins we left super annoyed. Sad to say the service was bad and I really just wanted a good meal on my last night in town.
Excellent food
Wonderful atmosphere wait staff was exelant hostess amazing
Excellent food and the best customer service 👍

Server Langston was awesome! Food great.  However, server Jasmine was little too comfy with a guest seated behind me. Heard more of their conversations (pleural ) than I needed to hear. Absolutely too much!  This continued during whole dinner meal. I wanted to call her out on this !  Her friend/other customer was dropping F bombs and was rude, loud and obnoxious!  I guess we could have asked to be moved to another table.  Let me state again, Langston was professional and very good server!  Jasmine should take note!

Was invited to a going away dinner here and I must say it was quite the tasty treat. I loved every single dish I tried. My favorite appetizers were the bacon and cheddar croquettes and the lobster mac and cheese. My entree was also excellent. I chose the Angus filet which was cooked and seasoned to perfection. As if that was not enough my side was a tasty dish of fried brussel sprouts with manchego cheese. While I'm not a fan of Brussels I must say these were great. All of this was followed by 3 different deserts shared by the table. We all had the chance to partake in a bit of bunny bread pudding topped with PB ice cream,  creme brulee and a delicious cheesecake. Even the coffee that accompanied our desert was great. The steakhouse is a must try! We had two great servers. Jasmine was an excellent server. Her great personality made the whole meal even more excellent. Anthony was also excellent and explained each dish to the table. Will return again!!!😍😍😍👌👌👌

The atmosphere, food, drinks and service were FIRST CLASS. What a wonderful experience. Jazmine and Anthony were marvelous.  What a plus to be able to stroll through the casino, have fun, and hear great music before and after an awesome meal. Win Win Win!
Great dining experience!
Good neighborhood spot to eat indoors or outdoors.
Great food, Wonderful service
Eric our server was really nice the scenery was beautiful and the food was amazing we will definitely be going back again
Good food.  Pricey for the smallish portions.   No MSG which is great.
Loved it!
What a wonderful experience! RUBY WAS THE BEST.

From the Hostess at the front to our waiter everybody was amazing.  The steak and asparagus it was so delicious that I can't wait to go back to this place.  My boyfriends birthday was this day and they surprised him with a Happy Birthday plate with 2 cheesecake samples.  I recommend this place and if I can give them 10 Stars I would!!!
Excellent food and the staff was so wonderful!!
Wonderful experience

Awesome service.  Needs to ask customers what they would like to see on menu.  Got rid of the short ribs which was the best thing they had on the menu.  Manager is friendly and AWESOME!
I would have given it three stars, but the staff was great. For the price I would go elsewhere.

Great food and perfect service. Meals Ala cart so average person will spend about $75. Crab cake appetizer was fantastic. But you only get one crab cake. My husband and I split a ribeye as it was a pound! Excellent sides. Suggest making a reservation.

The food tasted good, however the portion sizes were small. We were told that the side items would be enough for the table, but after paying $10 for some asparagus it was barely enough for us to each have a spear. I could have cooked the same dish for way cheaper at the house. I cannot believe I paid $36 for a small piece of tenderloin. Again I could have spent way less and been more satisfied at home. Bottom line is, I hate to spend that kind of money and still be hungry afterwards.

FANTASTIC food and service!

If you love cold steaks sent back twice, being billed for items sent back, eating alone while your girlfriends cold steaks come back cold again, and watching other tables send back food as well then please go eat here.

With or without the Besh name, the food and service are very similar. The 3 star rating is meant as 4-minus. Management steps in when service or quality falters. Food is prepared as designed, but sometimes doesn't make it to the table in that condition. Timing has been a problem in some of our visits there.

We had such a great time. The food and atmosphere was amazing. The crab cake was filling and the best I've ever had. The mac&cheese needed a bit more flavor but it wasn't horrible.  Danny gave such wonderful conversation aka Mr. Dirtybird. Mark made an amazing Harras-cane drink that was to die for. If you don't really like drinking bc you don't like the taste of alchohol please try this. He will be on cmvacation so try him when he gets back in a week or so. I felt like I net with friends with the staff and I will recommend this location to everyone. I hate I can't remember my servers name :( I know she studied/lived in Atlanta. Awesome staff great atmosphere I will be back.
Excellent service and the food was outstanding!  Highly recommended this place to anyone!
Wonderful food and atmosphere.  Great service!

Excellent shrimp and grits starter followed by delicious sea bass!  Staff were all courteous and accommodating - of special note was Ann Marie, our server. Very professional and helpful!!
Excellent food. Tenderloin was perfect.  French onion soup was amazing. Service is 5 Star.  Manager never fails to stop by the table.

I am in awe of the great service and delectable cuisine!  My steak was cooked  to perfection it melted in my mouth - the baked seafood oysters were magnificent!  The chef especially prepared crab stuffed onion rings for our enjoyment... OM Goodness the 12 layer coconut cake will make your heart skip a beat 😊 this was an epic dinning experience 😍💕💖💕
Food was good served not so much...

Burgers we're good, we couldn't afford anything else there.  Our friends enjoyed their meals though.  The problem is the steaks are ridiculously large with a giant price tag to match.  I think they'd get more business in the casino if they changed the structure of the menu/servings.  The fries with the burgers were nothing to write home about.  Sorry my pics didn't come out.
Food and service was great
Ordered my tenderloin rare, with a lukewarm center, and got exactly what I wanted.  Fantastic food.  Wonderful, knowledgeable server.  Quite possibly the best steak I've ever had.

The Mother's Day Jazz Brunch was a hidden gem! This place has NOT suffered a bit since dropping the Besh name. Service was on point and we had a $50 pre fixe menu for brunch worth every penny! We were one of maybe 5 tables in the place for an incredible brunch! Will definetly go back. Oh and they do validate parking but make sure the hostess places the sticker in the right place on your parking ticket because it's all automated now and the machine read the wrong barcode and we had to call for assiatance. But it all worked out and we didn't have to pay the $30 it would have cost us to park.
I sat at the bar.  Didn't eat there

Food is great! Got a burger and the crab and corn risotto. It was AMAZING!! Best I have ever had! Being a higher end steakhouse, we were worried about service with o my ordering burgers, but the waitress treated us like we were ordering steaks. Great service and food

Dear Steak House,  We try to be fancy at some points of our lives and when we do. This is definitely the place to do it. It's very top notch on our low budget pockets. We are locals from the lower 9th Ward of New Orleans and we love to come here for special occasions. The food is excellent and the staff is A+ . We come right in every time just to sit at the bar with Mr. Mark , Mr. Billy and Mr. Patrick. They are apart of the reason we will definitely continue to return to The Steak House.
Food was good.service was not what I expected in an expensive steak house.
Good food noise and crowded
Bar staff is horrible.   Needs lots of attitude adjusting. They think it's all about them
Great food, great service

Top shelf service and food. I have always enjoyed dining here.  Todd does and excellent job taking care of you, always has what you need but isn't interuptive.  I can recommend the corn and crab bisque and the filet or ribeye (bone in) are amazing.
Good food

Used to be great, now it is beyond terrible! This picture is from a few months ago which was ok. But this time I had an a la carte filet that was not cooked to order and even if it had been, it was absolutely the worst steak I’ve ever eaten. There is a fast food restaurant with steak that is better which is sad and infuriating considering the price they charged. Until something drastic changes then you should avoid this place at all cost. I am from New Orleans and it is a shame that you are here giving our food a bad name.
Different take on steak and lobster but very filling

Where to start.... Service was slow but it was busy.  We waited 20 min for bread and then 30 before I receivced my first course and then another 30 for entrees.  My steak was ordered med and my fiance ordered hers at a med well temp.  Mine was extremely rare and hers was cooked well.  I ordered the 30 day aged  Strip and she had the filet.  They butterflied her filet which should NEVER happen at an upscale steakhouse.  The steak was thin without being butterflied.  I didn't have the time or energy for a re-cook. We ordered dessert to go and again inedible.  Creme brûlée that was shoved in a pint size ice cream carton.  No fresh fruit but stale, wet cookies. We frequented Besh often and have rarely had an issue.  I realize the menu and employees are the same from what I understand, but this meal was a disaster.  Photos available.  Harrah's Diamond Aspiration members.
Great food, great service, a little pricey

We had heard mixed reviews of Besh Steak, but wanted to try it out for ourselves. When we were sat at our table we noticed almost immediately that the restaurant decor and look was very outdated, kind of resembling a Piccadilly, and had no bathroom. Service was pretty decent, our BBQ shrimp, salads, and drinks came out very quickly and tasted great. We ordered the swordfish and 10 oz filet, the Swordfish went great with the potatoes and mixed beans it came with, the filet was cooked perfectly, but was dry, grainy, and lacked any real flavor. The asparagus that came with the steak was undercooked and was not served with any hollandaise sauce. Overall our experience was pretty alright, but definitely not worth $185.
Somewhat overpriced for the quality, hard to enjoy in a casino. Though if thats you jam you'll probably like it.
Love it
Wonderful meal, attentive service, great evening!

Very disappointed. Been going to Besh for years and seems like it's going downhill each time. Visited during Memorial Day weekend. One person in our party ordered a medium-rare, but it came out medium, almost medium-well.This is the same issue I had on another visit, steaks being over-cooked, not what was requested. I also agree with a previous reviewer questioning the quality of the meat. The steak we had was a little dry and tougher than ones we've had in the past.  We sat near the kitchen, where we could see the food expeditor. I noticed the expeditor touched every steak that came out of the kitchen with his bare fingers, between touching other surfaces with his hands. Did not see him wash his hands at any time. He also put his fingers in what looked like a baked potato. This is not very pleasant to watch, especially in front of the dining room. We go to Besh because we can use our comps from the casino.
Had an unbelievable steak
One of the best steaks I've ever had.
Wonderful food, wonderful service. All that I expected.  You all need to go here!!
Attentive staff, prices are expensive but when I want a cowboy steak. That's where I go

I've been a loyal customer for the 5 years I've lived in NOLA. I was sad that I actually ask during my dinner last week if John Besh really still owned the restaurant🙁 This 5 star location has suddenly become a two or to stretch it a three star dinner. CONS: 1- table napkins now look like we're getting ready for an outdoor picnic 2- the fine dining menus are now just a one piece sheet of plastic 3- my once top if the line filet is a chewy hunk of meat 4- ordered the once off the chart pork chop plate to find a chewy over cooked cut of meat with no greens as the menus still says it comes with. When I advised the Mgr that they forgot my greens I was told they made the decision to drop the spinach- REALLY?? Same awesome employees that seem embarrassed by the changes- yes I was told Besh still owns the place but not sure I believe it or he has stopped looking!! Very sad
very good, but expensive to me
Great steak house and friendly wait staff. Loved the rabbit.
I am so shocked by how awful the food was at a Besh restaurant! The meat was overcooked and over seasoned and the grits had to be the worst of my whole trip - very dry and again over seasoned.

Simply Amazing! From drink (dirty vodka martini) to appetizer (spicy lamb meatballs and then truffled deviled eggs with Louisiana caviar) to actual steak (14 oz. cast-iron seared prime rib with au poivre sauce), I was completely impressed. Besh exceeded all of my expectations- highly recommended!

Our waitress was great but our food (four medium rare steaks) took an hour to make it to the table. Once at the table they were unimpressive.  We requested to see the manager and she could care less to speak to us she also didn't attempt to fix the problem.  What a shame that such a beautiful restaurant with huge potential was such a disappointment.   Next time we'll walk across the street to Ruth's Chris.

my boyfriend and i had such a lovely meal. the tartar was nice as was the broccoli salad. our steak was cooked to protection. our server you was a delite. we couldn't have asked for a more friendly, attentive server.  thanks
Food was pretty good and they made a decent cocktail. The atmosphere is a little weird as it wants to be higher end but is open to the casino.

Don't know what all the bad experience is about, I have always enjoyed the food, service and friendly manner.I have eaten at some of the so called best steak houses in the country and Besh takes a back seat to no one. We will always go back.

Tried to reach Besh for assistance with some clients and Harrah's was impossible to get through. Why does this restaurant not have its own customer service line. Cumbersome system. Cancelled reservation and went with competitor nearby.

Excellent service and wonderful food!!! We went there to there for our 6th anniversary and was impressed! My husband said he had the best ribeye he ever had. We live in Columbus ohio but if I'm ever in town I would definitely be back. It's a must🖒🖒🖒👌
The wait staff was very kind do and helpful,  the stake was out of this world, great flavor tender.. hardly had to wait at all......

Ok, this is a restaurant in a casino so I didn't expect a lot although when there is the name of a famous chef attached you hope for the best.  Since it seemed as though all we did in New Orleans was eat, I wasn't too hungry which makes it difficult to know if the food isn't all that good or you just didn't care.  Our server was very nice and helpful and when I asked for a Chardonnay he brought me a very nice glass, not too oakey.  While we were looking at the menu he brought out a plate of buttery toasted crostini along with liver pate compliments of the chef.  Nice touch and it was really tasty.  I opted to have just a salad with butter lettuce, toasted nuts and dressing, way too big a portion and the dressing was over powering.  Instead of an entree I had Big Bad BBQed Oysters supposedly topped with crab.  Absolutely no flavor at all.  Not a success.  My husband had a steak which is said was ok but a bit over cooked.  If you're in the casino and want dinner, it's not bad and not expensive but I wouldn't go out of my way for the restaurant.
Steak overdone. Redo steak was tough & flavorless. Given a filet to go. Will try that. Third time trying this restaurant at Harrah's.  Would not recommend it.
not worth the money.
It's OK. The steak was flavorful but noting special. The service was lacking and the atmosphere didn't match the price.

Went to have a steak and a drink.  Ended up having a wonderful dining experience. The service was impeccable. The dinner roles were a little hard, but everything else was perfect. Had the big bad oysters and ribeye. I was not disappointed.  Just a great steakhouse.

The star is a mistake the first time we ate thereit was great. This time I would not go back the fried bread for the duck liver was too greasy,  bboth of our lobster had to be sent back not cooked and still on the second time still not cooked the oyster casino was great and so was the duck liver but I came eight hundred miles to eat there maybe the other two might be better
Good food very tasty steak Nice atmosphere

Sat at the bar, lousy bartender.. display bottles are covered in dust, as are the shelves the liquor sits on. Asked for medium well steak, came out well over done... not worth your time.. try LA Boca for an amazing steak
Terrible service. Terrible service. Terrible service starting from the host to the waitress to the manager. John Besh should be embarrassed to have his name on this restaurant.

Delicious food and excellent service at its location inside the Harrah's Casino.  Because they had to push our reservation back 30 min to accommodate a large event, they gave us a huge appetizer sampler for free.

Crawfish & Corn Bisque = 10+ Baked oysters = 2 Rib Eye was good.  = 6 Shrimp and grits were also just good. = 6 Dessert (white choc & bananas foster) = 8 Overall, I give the food a 2 for it was good but nothing spectacular.  Bill = $120 for 2 no drinks  The decor is nice but in a casino = 1 for us.  Too much smoke!  Service - I felt that we were forgotten about sometimes.  Besh needs to hire some bus boys to help the servers!  = 1
Worth every penny!
